meta {
  name: GET software-version update status (v1.15.0, OTA sensor)
  type: http
  seq: 7
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v1/vehicle-information/{{vin}}/software-version/update-status
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v1.15.0 (myskoda PR #541, Skoda app v8.10.0+) — software version +
  OTA update status.

  Response: {status: "NO_UPDATE_AVAILABLE" | "UPDATE_SUCCESSFUL" | ...,
  currentSoftwareVersion: "3.8", carCapturedTimestamp: "...",
  releaseNotesUrl: "https://..."}

  Drives sensor.software_version (DIAGNOSTIC) +
  binary_sensor.ota_update_available (UPDATE device class).

  Forward-compat: unknown enum values default to "update available"
  so we don't have to ship a release for every new server enum value.

  Implementation: hooked into get_status() gather() in skoda.py.
  Cross-brand support deferred — CARIAD-BFF + OLA don't yet expose
  this endpoint (Research 2026-05-02).
}
